LazyData: true
Description: Provides S4 classes and methods for conducting mediation analysis with multiply imputed datasets.
    Integrates with the 'mice' package for multiple imputation and supports structural equation modeling (SEM)
    using either 'lavaan' or 'OpenMx'. Implements Rubin's rules for pooling parameter estimates and standard
    errors across imputations. Designed to work seamlessly with 'RMediation' for computing confidence intervals
    of indirect effects in the presence of missing data.
